  • Method Details

    • combineOneOrMore

      @SafeVarargs public static <T> List<T> combineOneOrMore(T first, T... rest)
      Convert variadic arguments with an enforced first element into a list of those elements.

      This pattern is used to ensure vararg overloads take at least one element, by enforcing this at compile-time.

      Type Parameters:
      T - the type of the elements.
      Parameters:
      first - the enforced first element.
      rest - the rest of the elements.
      Returns:
      the list of the elements.

    • requireNonNullValues

      public static <T extends Iterable<?>> T requireNonNullValues(T collection, String collectionName)
      Ensure there are no null elements in the given collection.

      This also ensures the iterable itself is not null either.

      Type Parameters:
      T - the input collection type.
      Parameters:
      collection - the iterable to check.
      collectionName - the name to give in the error message if anything is null.
      Returns:
      the input iterable type.

    • requireNonNullValues

      public static <T> T[] requireNonNullValues(T[] array, String arrayName)
      Ensure there are no null elements in the given array.

      This also ensures the array itself is not null either.

      Type Parameters:
      T - the input collection type.
      Parameters:
      array - the array to check.
      arrayName - the name to give in the error message if anything is null.
      Returns:
      the input array.
